[[File:Sakatokejinja01n4592.jpg|thumb|240px|{{ill|Sanjagu|ja|三社宮}}]]
[[File:Sakatokejinja04 1024.jpg|thumb|240px|{{ill|Mikoshi Storehouse|ja|神輿庫}}]]

'''Sakatoke Shrine''' (自玉手祭来酒解神社, たまでよりまつりきたるさかとけじんじゃ) is a {{ill|Shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Kyoto Prefecture|ja|京都府}}, {{ill|Otokun District|ja|乙訓郡}}, {{ill|Ōyamazaki Town|ja|大山崎町}}. Its common name is '''Sakatoke Shrine''' (酒解神社, さかとけじんじゃ, さかときじんじゃ). It is situated near the summit of {{ill|Tennozan|ja|天王山}}. It is listed as a {{ill|Shikinai Shrine|ja|延喜式神名帳|lt=Meishindai|lt_ja=名神大}}, and in the old {{ill|Modern Shrine Ranking system|ja|近代社格制度}} it was designated as a Gōsha.

==祭神==
It enshrines {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇神}} as its main deity and {{ill|Susanoo|ja|スサノオ|lt=Susanoo|lt_ja=素盞嗚尊}} as its secondary deity.

==歴史==
The origins of its founding are unclear; however, a ridge plaque dating to the first year of the {{ill|Yōrō|ja|養老}} era ({{ill|717 AD|ja|717年}}) indicates that it was established during the {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代}}. It was formerly known as Yamazaki no Mori (山埼杜) and was enshrined at the site of the present {{ill|Rikyū Hachiman Shrine|ja|離宮八幡宮}}. In the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代}}, the {{ill|Engi Shiki Shinmei-chō|ja|延喜式神名帳}} recorded the name as “Yamashiro Province, Otokun District, Sakatoke Shrine, formerly Yamazaki no Mori,” listing it among the state-sponsored {{ill|Meishindai Shrine|ja|名神大社}} and noting that offerings for the monthly and New Rice Festival were entrusted to it.

Subsequently, the enshrinement at Sakatoke Shrine lapsed, and its whereabouts were unknown until the Meiji period. The present Sakatoke Shrine was formerly the Yamazaki Tenno Shrine, which enshrined the deity Tenno Hachijōjin ({{ill|Gyūto Tennō|ja|牛頭天王}}) that had been venerated near the summit of Tennozan since medieval times. Although Tennozan was originally called Yamazaki-yama, it came to be known as Tennozan in association with this shrine. In June of the 10th year of the {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治}}, the Yamazaki Tenno Shrine was recognized as a Shikinai Shrine and renamed Sakatoke Shrine. The current main deity, Ōyamatsumi, was designated at that time.

The shrine’s mikoshi storehouse has been designated as an important cultural property by the nation.

==文化財==
* Honden – Registered Tangible Cultural Property of the nation ({{ill|Registered Tangible Cultural Property|ja|登録有形文化財}})
* Mikoshi storehouse – Important Cultural Property of the nation; an Itakura structure from the {{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代}}
* Mikoshi (2 units) – Works dating from before the {{ill|Muromachi period|ja|室町時代}}

==摂末社==
* Guardian Shrine: {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主|lt=Ōkuninushi|lt_ja=大己貴命}}
* Palace Master Shrine: {{ill|Ashinazuchi and Tenazuchi|ja|アシナヅチ・テナヅチ|lt=Ashinazuchi, Tenazuchi|lt_ja=足名稚命、手名稚命}}
* Three Shrines (Sanjagu):
** {{ill|Amaterasu Ōmikami Shrine|ja|天照大神}} 
** {{ill|Tsukuyomi Shrine|ja|ツクヨミ|lt=Tsukuyomi, Great Deity|lt_ja=月讀大神}}
** {{ill|Hiruko Shrine|ja|Hiruko|lt=Hiruko|lt_ja=蛭子神}}
* Itsukushima Shrine: {{ill|Ichikishimahime Shrine|ja|イチキシマヒメ|lt=Ichikishimahime|lt_ja=市杵嶌姫命}}

==行事==
* {{ill|Annual Festival|ja|例祭}} – May 3 to 5 (the mikoshi procession takes place on May 5 every other year)
* New Year’s Festival – December 31

==交通アクセス==
* {{ill|Hankyu Kyoto Main Line|ja|阪急京都本線|lt=Hankyu Kyoto Line|lt_ja=阪急京都線}} {{ill|Ōyamazaki Station|ja|大山崎駅}} – 40-minute walk
* {{ill|JR Kyoto Line|ja|JR京都線}} {{ill|Yamazaki Station (Kyoto Prefecture)|ja|山崎駅 (京都府)|lt=Yamazaki Station|lt_ja=山崎駅}} – 40-minute walk

==周辺情報==
* Ruins of the {{ill|Battle of Yamazaki|ja|山崎の戦い|lt=Battle of Yamazaki|lt_ja=山崎の合戦}}
* Tomb of the {{ill|Seventeen Martyrs|ja|十七烈士}}
* {{ill|Rikyū Hachiman Shrine|ja|離宮八幡宮}} (Aburaza)
* {{ill|Myōki-an|ja|妙喜庵}}
** {{ill|Taian|ja|待庵}}
* {{ill|Ōyamazaki Sansō Art Museum|ja|大山崎山荘美術館}}
* {{ill|Ōyamazaki Town Historical Museum|ja|大山崎町歴史資料館}}
* {{ill|Dainen-ji Temple|ja|大念寺 (京都府大山崎町)|lt=Dainen-ji|lt_ja=大念寺}}
* {{ill|Yamazaki Seitten|ja|山崎聖天}}
* {{ill|Hōshaku-ji|ja|宝積寺}}
* {{ill|Ōyamazaki Tile Kiln Ruins|ja|大山崎瓦窯跡}} (National {{ill|Historic Site|ja|史跡}})
* {{ill|Suntory}} {{ill|Yamazaki Distillery|ja|山崎蒸溜所}}

=== 関連項目 ===
* {{ill|Umenomiya Shrine|ja|梅宮大社}} – A shrine in Kyoto’s Ukyo Ward enshrining the same deity, Sakatoke, and is sometimes considered to be related.

