==歴史== The origins of its founding are unclear; however, a ridge plaque dating to the first year of the [[:en:Yōrō|Yōrō]] era ([[:en:717|717 AD]]) indicates that it was established during the [[:en:Nara period|Nara period]]. It was formerly known as Yamazaki no Mori (山埼杜) and was enshrined at the site of the present {{ill|Rikyū Hachiman Shrine|ja|離宮八幡宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rikyū Hachiman Shrine|qq=|1=Rikyū Hachiman-gū|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11659484}}. In the [[:en:Heian period|Heian period]], the {{ill|Engi Shiki Shinmei-chō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engi Shiki Shinmei-chō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} recorded the name as “Yamashiro Province, Otokun District, Sakatoke Shrine, formerly Yamazaki no Mori,” listing it among the state-sponsored {{ill|Meishindai Shrine|ja|名神大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meishindai Shrine|qq=|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=Myojin Taisha|WD=Q9610964}} and noting that offerings for the monthly and New Rice Festival were entrusted to it.
Subsequently, the enshrinement at Sakatoke Shrine lapsed, and its whereabouts were unknown until the Meiji period. The present Sakatoke Shrine was formerly the Yamazaki Tenno Shrine, which enshrined the deity Tenno Hachijōjin ([[:en:Gozu Tennō|Gozu Tennō]]) that had been venerated near the summit of Tennozan since medieval times. Although Tennozan was originally called Yamazaki-yama, it came to be known as Tennozan in association with this shrine. In June of the 10th year of the [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]], the Yamazaki Tenno Shrine was recognized as a Shikinai Shrine and renamed Sakatoke Shrine. The current main deity, Ōyamatsumi, was designated at that time.
The shrine’s mikoshi storehouse has been designated as an important cultural property by the nation.
